        <item>
            <title>0.3.539</title>
            <pubDate>Mon, 13 Jul 2026 19:10:08 -0700</pubDate>
            <sparkle:version>539</sparkle:version>
            <sparkle:shortVersionString>0.3.539</sparkle:shortVersionString>
            <sparkle:minimumSystemVersion>14.0</sparkle:minimumSystemVersion>
            <description><![CDATA[<h2>ChainLink 0.3.539</h2>
<p class="sub">Log rides by hand, import from Zwift &amp; more, elegant PDF reports, and a smarter bike fit.</p>

<h3>Log a ride — and import beyond FIT</h3>
<ul>
  <li><b>Log a Ride</b>: a new "＋ Add Ride" button on the Rides page lets you
  type a ride in by hand — duration, distance, a "Feel" scale (Easy → Max) that
  estimates your training load when there's no power or heart rate, plus an
  optional details drawer for power/HR/cadence/etc. It also edits an existing
  ride, so you can fix a bad import.</li>
  <li><b>Import TCX, GPX and CSV</b>, not just FIT: a Zwift or TrainerRoad TCX
  comes in complete (graphs, map and accurate TSS, like a FIT); a phone app's
  GPX and summary CSVs work too. Each lands in a review sheet, pre-filled, so
  you confirm or fill any gaps before it saves — and re-importing the same file
  won't duplicate it.</li>
  <li>The <b>Import window</b> got a full visual refresh to match the rest of
  the app.</li>
</ul>

<h3>Elegant PDF reports</h3>
<ul>
  <li>The <b>build report</b> and <b>bike-fit sheet</b> share one polished
  look — proper margins, page numbering, a date, and per-section subtotals.
  Choose <b>A4 or US&nbsp;Letter</b> in Settings. The fit sheet is now
  downloadable, not just shareable.</li>
  <li>The build report shows both an <b>actual cost</b> (every part) and your
  <b>cost to complete</b> (minus parts already in hand), in a more compact
  layout.</li>
</ul>

<h3>A sharper bike fit</h3>
<ul>
  <li>Measure saddle fore/aft from the <b>80&nbsp;mm biomechanical point</b>
  (where your sit bones load the saddle) instead of the fiddly nose — it's
  repeatable and survives a saddle swap. A guide helps you find the point, and
  the fit sheet prints an actual-size gauge.</li>
  <li><b>No mental arithmetic</b>: measurements that used to want a difference
  (setback, bar drop) now take two plain wall/floor readings and the app does
  the sum, showing its working.</li>
  <li>Your height and inseam show on the fit page, and every fit warning was
  audited so it no longer cries wolf on a correct measurement.</li>
</ul>

<h3>AI coach</h3>
<ul>
  <li>Fixed the coach failing to answer on newer Google Gemini models (a
  "thought signature" error) — the free Gemini option works again.</li>
</ul>

<h3>Also</h3>
<ul>
  <li>The bike <b>builder counts parts you need two of</b> (rotors, tyres,
  valves…) — automatically, or set any quantity by hand.</li>
  <li>The Rides toolbar is tidier on iPad, and cross-training activities in
  "Log a Ride" now follow the sports you enable in Settings.</li>
</ul>
]]></description>
